{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2c7857e0-ad9f-4fd6-af09-7d6b2d773e22","content":"Add a semi-transparent layer above the shader inside [web/src/components/dithering-background.tsx](web/src/components/dithering-background.tsx#L22). Smallest change: keep the shader as-is, then insert an absolute overlay div after it.\n\n```tsx\nreturn (\n  <div className=\"pointer-events-none fixed inset-0 -z-10\">\n    <Suspense fallback={<div className=\"absolute inset-0 bg-background\" />}>\n      <div\n        className=\"absolute inset-0 z-0 transition-[filter] duration-200\"\n        style={{ filter: \"blur(var(--dither-blur, 0px))\" }}\n      >\n        <Dithering\n          colorBack={colorBack}\n          colorFront={colorFront}\n          shape=\"warp\"\n          type=\"4x4\"\n          speed={0.2}\n          className=\"size-full\"\n          minPixelRatio={1}\n        />\n      </div>\n\n      <div className=\"absolute inset-0 z-10 bg-black/10\" />\n    </Suspense>\n  </div>\n);\n```\n\nUse `bg-black/10` for a light darkening, or bump it to `bg-black/15` or `bg-black/20` if you want it stronger. If you want the darkening to vary by theme, make that overlay conditional on `isDark`.\n\nBecause this component is mounted globally in the app shell and multiple pages, the change affects all screens that use [DitheringBackground](web/src/app/page.tsx#L260).","toolRequests":[],"reasoningText":""},"id":"e3a33e13-f2bd-4b91-8bca-63e37ab68f87","timestamp":"2026-05-21T09:20:55.482Z","parentId":"879aeb32-6986-4fab-897f-8cb47d06f673"}
